  </div></nav>

  <!-- Section 1: Cow Urine -->
  <section class="section" id="urine">
    <div class="text-block">
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Section 1</span>
        <h2>Cow Urine</h2>
        <h3>Key Background</h3>
        <p>The most valuable active substance in cow urine is <strong>urea</strong> — responsible for almost all therapeutic benefits, yet also the source of the smell. Urea itself is odourless; the strong scent appears only when bacteria break it down into ammonia. <strong>Our goal: eliminate the smell, but keep urea fully intact and active.</strong></p>
        <h3 style="margin-top:2rem;">What Existing Authorities Recommend — and Why We Do It Differently</h3>
        <p>Well-known authors advise using camphor or mint oil to mask odour. Camphor can actually speed up bacterial activity, accelerating breakdown of urea into ammonia. Mint is too light to cut through heavy ammonia-based odours. <em>Our recommendations eliminate odour completely, stop the reaction that creates smell, and fully preserve urea and all healing properties.</em></p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <h3>Top 5 Essential Oils — Ranked by Effectiveness</h3>
        <ul class="oil-list">
          <li>
            <div class="oil-rank">1</div>
            <div class="oil-content">
              <p class="dosage">2–3 drops per 100 ml</p>
              <h4>Lemongrass</h4>
              <p>Best overall: strong, fresh, citrus-woody scent. Contains citral, which kills bacteria, neutralises ammonia chemically, and stops the enzyme that breaks down urea. 100% safe, preserves all potency.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="oil-rank">2</div>
            <div class="oil-content">
              <p class="dosage">1–2 drops per 100 ml</p>
              <h4>Cedarwood (Himalayan / Atlas / Virginian)</h4>
              <p>Deep, warm, woody, very long-lasting. Heavy molecules form a protective barrier, slow evaporation, lock in active ingredients, and permanently bind odour molecules.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="oil-rank">3</div>
            <div class="oil-content">
              <p class="dosage">1–2 drops per 100 ml</p>
              <h4>Thyme (White / Red)</h4>
              <p>Powerful antibacterial and deodorising action. Very effective at neutralising heavy organic smells; gentle enough not to alter active compounds.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="oil-rank">4</div>
            <div class="oil-content">
              <p class="dosage">1 drop per 100 ml</p>
              <h4>Oregano</h4>
              <p>Extremely strong antimicrobial; cuts through ammonia and earthy odours instantly. Use slightly less — very potent.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="oil-rank">5</div>
            <div class="oil-content">
              <p class="dosage">2–3 drops per 100 ml</p>
              <h4>Tea Tree</h4>
              <p>Balanced, reliable, fresh-medicinal scent. Neutralises odour well and protects the chemical stability of the urine.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="blend-box">
          <h4>✅ Best Blend: Lemongrass + Cedarwood</h4>
          <p>Recommended ratio: 2 drops Lemongrass + 1 drop Cedarwood per 100 ml. Together: zero smell, 100% potency, and a pleasant, clean, fresh-woody aroma.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2rem;">Storage &amp; Shelf Life</h3>
        <ul class="apply-steps">
          <li><span class="step-num">1</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Preparation</strong><p>Add your chosen oil(s) first, swirl gently — do not shake vigorously.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="step-num">2</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Container</strong><p>Store in a dark, sealed glass jar or bottle, away from heat and sunlight.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="step-num">3</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Shelf Life</strong><p>Cow urine does not spoil quickly — it actually matures and improves over time. It remains fully effective for at least 1 year, and can keep its properties for several years when stored properly.</p></div></li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2rem;">How to Apply Cow Urine</h3>
        <ul class="apply-steps">
          <li><span class="step-num">1</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Apply to clean skin</strong><p>Face, neck, chest, arms, legs, or the whole body.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="step-num">2</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Massage gently</strong><p>Until fully absorbed or almost dry.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="step-num">3</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Leave on or rinse</strong><p>You may leave it on or rinse with water after 15–30 minutes. No soap needed.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Cow Dung -->
  <section class="section" id="dung" style="background:var(--cream-deep);">
    <div class="text-block">
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Section 2</span>
        <h2>Cow Dung</h2>
        <h3>Sourcing — What to Look For</h3>
        <p>Fresh dung from cows fed a clean, natural diet is always best. Organic dung from traditional Indian breeds such as Gir or Sahiwal has a naturally mild, earthy scent. Dung from standard dairy breeds may carry a stronger odour, yet it remains fully effective. Always collect fresh deposits, never old or aged piles. For the greatest energetic potency, source it from places where cows are treated with love and care — such as Hindu temples or traditional goshalas.</p>
        <h3 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Shelf Life &amp; Storage</h3>
        <p>Fresh cow dung retains its full quality for roughly <strong>one month</strong> at room temperature. Store in a small lidded jar. A <strong>100–300 mg portion</strong> is enough for 2–3 weeks of application. Replace with fresh dung every 2–3 weeks.</p>
        <h3 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Clothing</h3>
        <p>For regular practice wear <strong>dark-coloured underwear or pyjamas</strong>. Wool is ideal — it naturally regulates body temperature and helps manage odours.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <h3>The Smell — Complete Solutions</h3>
        <div class="method-card">
          <h4>Method 1: Let the Dung Dry on the Skin</h4>
          <p>Once dry, cow dung has almost no scent at all. Apply, massage in, and wait until fully dry. Speed drying with a hairdryer, or cover immediately with clothing — your body heat dries it in 5–15 minutes. Drying alone resolves 70–100% of the odour issue.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="method-card">
          <h4>Method 2: Use Essential Oils — Recommended</h4>
          <p>Add 2–5 drops of essential oil to the dung before applying. Use the same Top 5 oils from the Cow Urine section. Best choice: Lemongrass + Cedarwood blend.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="method-card">
          <h4>Method 3: Apply a Clay Top Layer</h4>
          <p>A thin layer of <strong>Gopi Chandan Tilak</strong> — the pure organic clay used by Krishna devotees, sourced from the banks of the River Ganga — creates a perfect seal, blocking all odour molecules. It is smooth, easy to apply, and has a gentle, pleasant fragrance.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2rem;">Application Methods</h3>
        <div class="method-card">
          <h4>Basic Application: Apply and Wash Off</h4>
          <p>Apply a small amount of fresh dung — about the size of half a walnut. Rub between your palms, then spread lightly over the skin. Massage gently for 5–15 minutes. Rinse off with <strong>water only — do not use soap.</strong></p>
          <p>The first benefits you will notice are improved mood, easier breathing, and deeper, more vivid dreams.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="method-card">
          <h4>Extended Application: Apply and Leave On</h4>
          <p>Apply a thin layer, then immediately put on your dedicated dark cotton pyjamas. Within 5–15 minutes the dung dries and any remaining odour disappears. A thin coating is always enough — regularity matters far more than thickness.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="method-card">
          <h4>Shared Bathrooms — Managing the Brief Window</h4>
          <p>Apply in your bedroom and rinse off in the bathroom later. A quick spray of room fragrance covers any trace. If you add the recommended essential oils, you will avoid this issue entirely.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="note-box"><p>The first time you hold fresh cow dung, you may feel a moment of resistance. That is not your body reacting — it is social conditioning. Once you experience the benefits, any hesitation will vanish completely.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: Combined -->
  <section class="section" id="combined">
    <div class="text-block">
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Section 3</span>
        <h2>Combined Application</h2>
        <p>Using both together gives you the full synergy of their healing properties. <strong>Always add your chosen essential oils to the urine and/or dung first</strong>, before mixing or applying.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
        <div class="method-card">
          <h4>Method 1: Layered Application</h4>
          <ul class="apply-steps" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
            <li><span class="step-num">1</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Prepare</strong><p>Add essential oils to the cow urine in advance.</p></div></li>
            <li><span class="step-num">2</span><div class="step-content"><strong>First layer</strong><p>Apply cow urine to the skin and massage thoroughly until almost dry — leave it slightly damp. This wetness acts as a natural carrier, making it easier to spread the dung.</p></div></li>
            <li><span class="step-num">3</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Second layer</strong><p>Apply a thin coat of cow dung directly over the slightly damp urine layer. Spread evenly.</p></div></li>
            <li><span class="step-num">4</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Seal</strong><p>Once the dung starts to dry, apply a fine layer of Gopi Chandan Tilak clay over the top.</p></div></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="method-card">
          <h4>Method 2: Mixed Application</h4>
          <ul class="apply-steps" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
            <li><span class="step-num">1</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Prepare</strong><p>Add essential oils to the cow urine first.</p></div></li>
            <li><span class="step-num">2</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Mix</strong><p>Combine fresh cow urine and cow dung in a small container and stir until you have a smooth, consistent paste.</p></div></li>
            <li><span class="step-num">3</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Apply</strong><p>Massage the mixture onto your skin in a thin, even layer.</p></div></li>
            <li><span class="step-num">4</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Dry &amp; Seal</strong><p>Let it air dry until almost dry, then finish with a light layer of Gopi Chandan Tilak clay on top.</p></div></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Ghee -->
  <section class="section" id="ghee" style="background:var(--cream-deep);">
    <div class="text-block">
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Section 4</span>
        <h2>Cow Ghee</h2>
        <p>Ghee is known in Ayurveda as the "carrier of potency" — it nourishes, protects, and helps other active substances absorb more deeply. Safe, gentle, and suitable for all ages and skin types.</p>
        <h3 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Internal Use</h3>
        <ul class="apply-steps">
          <li><span class="step-num">1</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Daily nourishment</strong><p>Start with ½ to 1 teaspoon taken first thing in the morning on an empty stomach, or added to warm water, herbal tea, or warm milk. 1–2 teaspoons per day is usually enough.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="step-num">2</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Cooking</strong><p>Use as your main cooking fat. High smoke point — does not break down or form harmful compounds when heated.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
        <h3 style="margin-top:2rem;">Abhyanga — Full-Body Massage</h3>
        <ul class="apply-steps">
          <li><span class="step-num">1</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Warm the ghee</strong><p>Gently in a cup or your palms until it turns liquid.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="step-num">2</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Apply all over the body</strong><p>Use long, smooth strokes on arms and legs, and soft circular motions on joints, chest, and abdomen.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="step-num">3</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Leave on for 15 to 30 minutes</strong><p>This gives it time to absorb and soften the skin.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="step-num">4</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Rinse off</strong><p>With warm water. You can use a mild, natural cleanser or simply wipe away excess with a warm cloth.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
        <h3 style="margin-top:2rem;">Storage &amp; Shelf Life</h3>
        <p>Keep in a clean, dry, sealed glass jar away from direct sunlight. When pure and properly made, ghee remains stable for <strong>6–12 months at room temperature</strong>, and can last <strong>several years</strong> in a cool, dark place.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: Panchagavya -->
  <section class="section" id="panchagavya">
    <div class="text-block">
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Section 5</span>
        <h2>Panchagavya Application</h2>
        <p>Panchagavya is a complete preparation combining all five cow products. Correct preparation and maturation are essential.</p>
        <h3 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Traditional Preparation Ratio</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal">
        <table class="ratio-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>Parts</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Cow Dung</td><td>5 parts</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Cow Urine</td><td>5 parts</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Cow Milk</td><td>2 parts</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Curd</td><td>2 parts</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Ghee</td><td>1 part</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <ul class="apply-steps">
          <li><span class="step-num">1</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Mix all ingredients</strong><p>In a clean glass or earthenware jar.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="step-num">2</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Add essential oils</strong><p>2–3 drops Lemongrass + 1–2 drops Cedarwood per 100 ml total volume.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="step-num">3</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Stir gently</strong><p>Once or twice daily. Cover loosely — do not seal airtight, as natural fermentation occurs.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="step-num">4</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Mature</strong><p>Leave in a cool, shaded place for 7 to 14 days.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="step-num">5</span><div class="step-content"><strong>Seal and store</strong><p>Once matured. Remains effective for many months to over a year.</p></div></li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2rem;">Topical Application</h3>
        <div class="method-card"><h4>As a paste</h4><p>Apply a thin layer over the skin and massage gently. Leave for 15–30 minutes, then rinse with warm water only.</p></div>
        <div class="method-card"><h4>As a compress</h4><p>Dilute 1 part Panchagavya with 3–4 parts clean water. Soak a cloth and apply to the area of need.</p></div>
        <div class="method-card"><h4>Sealing</h4><p>For longer application, finish with a light layer of Gopi Chandan Tilak clay to lock in all benefits.</p></div>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2rem;">Internal Use — Traditional Only</h3>
        <div class="warning-box">
          <p><strong>Only use fully matured preparations</strong> — never take fresh, unfermented mixtures internally. Start with 1 teaspoon per day on an empty stomach. Consult a qualified Ayurvedic practitioner if you have existing health conditions.</p>
        </div>
        <h3 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Storage &amp; Shelf Life</h3>
        <p>Keep in a clean, dark glass jar sealed tightly once fully matured. When prepared correctly, Panchagavya improves with age and remains effective for <strong>up to 1–2 years</strong>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

